{
  "name": "Snapping Crab",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "modules/pf1spheres/assets/icons/spheres/dual_wielding.webp",
  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>While in this stance, whenever you miss a creature with a melee attack made as part of a dual attack, the first melee attack that creature makes against you until the beginning of your next turn provokes an attack of opportunity from you. You must make the attack of opportunity with a melee weapon you missed the creature with during your dual attack, and the attack suffers the same penalties as it did during the dual attack. You may not use this talent in conjunction with (deflect) talents or any other ability that would grant you an attack or combat maneuver due to a missed attack against you.</p>\n",
